### 1. Admin Login (Generates and saves the Admin Token)
POST http://localhost:8080/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "admin123"
}

> {%
    // This saves the token from the response into a global variable
    client.global.set("admin_token", response.body.token);
    client.test("Request executed successfully", function() {
        client.assert(response.status === 200, "Response status is not 200");
    });
%}

### 2. Admin Add Employee (Uses the saved Admin Token)
POST http://localhost:8080/admin/add
Authorization: Bearer {{admin_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser_intellij",
  "password": "test123",
  "role": "EMPLOYEE"
}

### 3. Admin Accessing Employee Route (Expect 403 Forbidden)
GET http://localhost:8080/employee/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{admin_token}}


### 4. Employee Login (Generates and saves the Employee Token)
POST http://localhost:8080/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "employee",
  "password": "emp123"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("emp_token", response.body.token);
%}

### 5. Employee Accessing Employee Route (Expect 200 OK)
GET http://localhost:8080/employee/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{emp_token}}


### 6. No Token Provided (Expect 401/403 Forbidden)
GET http://localhost:8080/employee/profile